D. Probabilities

Compute the probability that a randomly selected commune with elevation over 2000 is from the canton of Valais.

In[31]:
all_communes_in_valais_with_elevation_over_two_thousand = df[
    (df["Elevation"] > 2000)].groupby("Canton").get_group("VS").count()["Commune"]

all_communes_with_elevation_over_two_thousand = df[
    (df["Elevation"] > 2000)].count()["Commune"]

print(f"The probability of randomly selecting a commune in the canton of Valais with an\
 elevation over \ntwo thousand is\
 {all_communes_in_valais_with_elevation_over_two_thousand / all_communes_with_elevation_over_two_thousand}.")

The probability of randomly selecting a commune in the canton of Valais with an elevation over 
two thousand is 0.5104166666666666.
